<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id525ab487-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s482"><num value="482">§ 482.</num><heading> Definitions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">As used in this chapter, the term “judicial officer” means a United States district court judge or a United States magistrate judge.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id525ab488-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/101/650/tI/s103/a">Pub. L. 101–650, title I, § 103(a)</ref>, title III, § 321, <date date="1990-12-01">Dec. 1, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/5096">104 Stat. 5096</ref>, 5117.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id525ab489-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id525ab48a-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I78" topic="changeOfName" id="id525ab48b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Change of Name</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">“United States magistrate judge” substituted for “United States magistrate” in text pursuant to <ref href="/us/pl/101/650/s321">section 321 of Pub. L. 101–650</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t28/s631">section 631 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
